1
00:00:00,805 --> 00:00:32,805
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:40,849
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,849 --> 00:00:42,661
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:45,196 --> 00:00:47,096
It was two lines.

5
00:00:48,362 --> 00:00:49,729
That day.

6
00:00:49,729 --> 00:00:52,005
That night, that man.

7
00:00:52,005 --> 00:00:54,373
[Chapter 1 Fateful Encounter]

8
00:00:59,621 --> 00:01:03,029
[4 Weeks Ago]

9
00:01:12,773 --> 00:01:15,062
[Episode 1]

10
00:01:47,129 --> 00:01:48,996
Hui Won, did you get in safely?

11
00:01:48,996 --> 00:01:51,829
Of course. All thanks to someone
personally putting a wig on me.

12
00:01:51,829 --> 00:01:54,062
Sorry, you know how my dad is.

13
00:01:54,062 --> 00:01:56,629
He acts like his life goal
is marrying his daughter off well.

14
00:01:56,629 --> 00:01:58,396
He can't stand seeing me skip events.

15
00:01:58,396 --> 00:02:01,796
He knows this place is basically
a solo party for the young and rich.

16
00:02:01,796 --> 00:02:05,762
Anyway, don't worry about me.
Just go enjoy your favorite concert.

17
00:02:05,762 --> 00:02:08,629
Whether in college or now,
you go crazy for MeloMance.

18
00:02:08,629 --> 00:02:10,096
They're so sweet.

19
00:02:10,096 --> 00:02:12,229
Sweetness is poison to me.

20
00:02:12,229 --> 00:02:14,862
Hey, why don't you look around
for a decent guy yourself?

21
00:02:14,862 --> 00:02:17,762
- Let's end your lifelong singlehood.
- Ugh, no thanks.

22
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:19,629
I'll just have a beer and leave.

23
00:02:19,629 --> 00:02:21,662
Excuse me...

24
00:02:21,662 --> 00:02:24,262
Hold on, I'll call you back later.

25
00:02:25,029 --> 00:02:27,529
- Yes?
- We're running a survey for a company event.

26
00:02:27,529 --> 00:02:31,662
'Cherry Blossom Wedding' is
the concept. Want to join?

27
00:02:31,662 --> 00:02:32,997
[Marriage Fantasy Test]

28
00:02:39,365 --> 00:02:40,829
[Marriage Fantasy Test]

29
00:02:40,829 --> 00:02:43,696
A world where marriage is
a choice, not a requirement.

30
00:02:43,696 --> 00:02:46,062
If someone asks me about marriage...

31
00:02:46,062 --> 00:02:50,462
Choose when you dream of getting married?

32
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:51,462
[Immediately, if I'm ready;
After becoming financially stable]

33
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:52,462
[After achieving my goals;
When my partner seems ready]

34
00:02:52,462 --> 00:02:53,957
[When I don't want to
be apart from them; Other]

35
00:02:59,829 --> 00:03:01,562
I can say for sure.

36
00:03:01,562 --> 00:03:03,685
I won't get married in this lifetime.

37
00:03:04,869 --> 00:03:11,685
[In the next life]

38
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:17,929
[Team Leader Bang]

39
00:03:22,396 --> 00:03:23,429
Yes, Team Leader Bang.

40
00:03:23,429 --> 00:03:26,496
Does yesterday's PPT
include the Q4 work plan?

41
00:03:26,496 --> 00:03:29,229
Weren't we supposed to add that
at the end of the month?

42
00:03:29,229 --> 00:03:31,562
We need it for Monday's team leader meeting.

43
00:03:31,562 --> 00:03:33,362
So, revise it and email it to me by tomorrow.

44
00:03:33,362 --> 00:03:34,462
By tomorrow?

45
00:03:34,462 --> 00:03:38,496
Yeah, I've got something urgent today. Sorry.

46
00:03:38,496 --> 00:03:40,129
Thank you.

47
00:03:40,129 --> 00:03:42,162
Wow, so many good-looking men here!

48
00:03:42,162 --> 00:03:46,029
Having a good cousin really pays off.

49
00:03:46,029 --> 00:03:48,529
Why is Team Leader Bang here...

50
00:03:51,196 --> 00:03:53,929
Could she be starting strange rumors at work?

51
00:03:56,629 --> 00:03:59,562
Excuse me, could you back me up?

52
00:03:59,562 --> 00:04:01,462
What are you doing?

53
00:04:01,462 --> 00:04:03,396
Who are you?

54
00:04:03,396 --> 00:04:06,862
My darling, even your smile is adorable.

55
00:04:06,862 --> 00:04:08,229
Oh, dear.

56
00:04:08,229 --> 00:04:10,149
[Chapter 2 Coincidence]

57
00:04:54,729 --> 00:04:56,396
Oh, Du Jun.

58
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:58,329
Hello.

59
00:04:58,329 --> 00:05:00,596
Well, look who's early...

60
00:05:00,596 --> 00:05:03,629
No, I should be formal here, Director.

61
00:05:03,629 --> 00:05:05,762
Cut it out. No need between us.

62
00:05:05,762 --> 00:05:07,196
Ah, I see all the sons and daughters

63
00:05:07,196 --> 00:05:10,962
from J Land, Sangwoo Electronics,
and Semo Corporation are present.

64
00:05:10,962 --> 00:05:12,496
Go on, go greet them too.

65
00:05:12,496 --> 00:05:14,229
There must be friends you met
while studying abroad, right?

66
00:05:14,229 --> 00:05:16,329
That's exactly why I'm avoiding them.

67
00:05:16,329 --> 00:05:19,462
Just 30 minutes. I'll leave
in exactly 30 minutes.

68
00:05:19,462 --> 00:05:20,496
Since when do you last 30 minutes?

69
00:05:20,496 --> 00:05:22,062
If I can endure just 30 minutes,

70
00:05:22,062 --> 00:05:25,896
then she'll never
bring up the blind dates again...

71
00:05:26,529 --> 00:05:27,629
- Why?
- A big catch!

72
00:05:27,629 --> 00:05:29,962
Looks like you got tricked by her again.

73
00:05:29,962 --> 00:05:32,262
Tricked? So, you need to handle this well.

74
00:05:32,262 --> 00:05:35,462
You're here as a witness.

75
00:05:35,462 --> 00:05:37,762
I wondered why you invited me.

76
00:05:37,762 --> 00:05:39,662
You...

77
00:05:39,662 --> 00:05:40,696
What?

78
00:05:40,696 --> 00:05:45,696
As your secretary,
I must be an excellent witness.

79
00:05:45,696 --> 00:05:47,196
Stop looking at me like that. It's stressful.

80
00:05:47,196 --> 00:05:49,896
Don't you know I get a sensitive
stomach when I'm stressed?

81
00:05:49,896 --> 00:05:51,829
If you don't know... oh, no.

82
00:05:51,829 --> 00:05:53,296
Nature's calling. Bathroom...

83
00:05:53,296 --> 00:05:54,796
You can stay here by yourself, right?

84
00:05:54,796 --> 00:05:56,729
Bathroom...

85
00:05:56,729 --> 00:05:58,904
Where are you going alone?

86
00:05:58,904 --> 00:06:03,141
You've gotten so much more attractive.

87
00:06:03,141 --> 00:06:05,093
Maybe, you should make a move on...

88
00:06:05,093 --> 00:06:07,429
I'm not sure what I'm here for.

89
00:06:13,662 --> 00:06:16,596
Excuse me, could you back me up?

90
00:06:16,596 --> 00:06:18,562
What are you doing?

91
00:06:18,562 --> 00:06:20,562
Who are you?

92
00:06:20,562 --> 00:06:23,929
My darling, even your smile is adorable.

93
00:06:23,929 --> 00:06:25,762
Oh, dear.

94
00:06:25,762 --> 00:06:27,429
What are you doing right now?

95
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:31,262
How is your skin so baby-soft?

96
00:06:33,296 --> 00:06:34,596
What? You're hungry?

97
00:06:34,596 --> 00:06:38,053
Shall we go get something
delicious over there?

98
00:06:38,053 --> 00:06:41,029
- Oh.
- I said what are you doing?

99
00:06:41,029 --> 00:06:44,829
Well... the thing is...

100
00:06:45,562 --> 00:06:47,696
Huh?

101
00:06:47,696 --> 00:06:48,696
Your cheeks are red.

102
00:06:48,696 --> 00:06:52,496
Oh, I'll go get you something cool.

103
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:54,596
No, hey, wait...

104
00:06:59,129 --> 00:07:01,396
Here's grape juice...

105
00:07:19,288 --> 00:07:21,093
Oh!

106
00:07:32,996 --> 00:07:34,129
Oh, no.

107
00:07:34,129 --> 00:07:35,996
Are you okay?

108
00:07:38,362 --> 00:07:40,062
Oh no, oh no.

109
00:07:40,062 --> 00:07:41,862
- Napkin, napkin!
- Stop it.

110
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:46,596
I'll just go to the restroom
and bring it right back.

111
00:07:46,596 --> 00:07:48,329
Enough!

112
00:07:54,429 --> 00:07:56,325
[Chapter 3 Inevitability]

113
00:08:04,196 --> 00:08:08,596
Wow, I never thought I'd see Kang Du Jun
wearing this kind of outfit.

114
00:08:08,596 --> 00:08:10,029
Seriously, this is all
the clothes you've got?

115
00:08:10,029 --> 00:08:12,529
And why on earth do you
have this silly outfit in your car?

116
00:08:12,529 --> 00:08:13,996
My oldest nephew bought it for me.

117
00:08:13,996 --> 00:08:16,829
Let's not bring family into this.

118
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:20,596
Well, I heard this kind of silly outfit
is trending these days.

119
00:08:20,596 --> 00:08:24,229
Geez, that woman has some nerve.

120
00:08:24,229 --> 00:08:26,996
She actually got Kang Du Jun
all worked up and ran off.

121
00:08:26,996 --> 00:08:29,362
Never bring that up in front of me again.

122
00:08:29,362 --> 00:08:30,396
It just came back to me.

123
00:08:30,396 --> 00:08:32,396
Ah, sorry.

124
00:08:33,929 --> 00:08:35,296
But, it hasn't even been 30 minutes.

125
00:08:35,296 --> 00:08:37,229
It's okay to leave now, right?

126
00:08:37,229 --> 00:08:39,262
You expect me to stay like this
for another 20 minutes?

127
00:08:39,262 --> 00:08:41,762
Right, I wouldn't last there either.

128
00:08:41,762 --> 00:08:45,329
But seriously, why don't you
want to get married?

129
00:08:46,096 --> 00:08:49,462
Don't tell me you're weighing
marriage efficiency or something?

130
00:08:49,462 --> 00:08:50,729
Why wouldn't I?

131
00:08:50,729 --> 00:08:53,062
Think of the time and cost spent dating,
dining, and having coffee.

132
00:08:53,062 --> 00:08:55,329
Plus all that unnecessary emotional labor
you'd have to endure.

133
00:08:55,329 --> 00:08:57,796
When I'm already short on work hours
and stealing from sleep,

134
00:08:57,796 --> 00:09:00,829
why invest in such inefficiency?

135
00:09:00,829 --> 00:09:02,829
Alright, I get it.

136
00:09:02,829 --> 00:09:07,629
Convince your mom efficiently on your own.

137
00:09:07,629 --> 00:09:08,997
Yellow tee.

138
00:09:12,396 --> 00:09:14,796
This is hilarious.

139
00:09:17,529 --> 00:09:20,005
Enough!

140
00:09:20,005 --> 00:09:21,296
Oh, my.

141
00:09:21,296 --> 00:09:23,529
So? You just ran away like that?

142
00:09:23,529 --> 00:09:24,529
Ugh, I don't know.

143
00:09:24,529 --> 00:09:27,429
When I came back with tissues
and dry-cleaning money, he was already gone.

144
00:09:27,429 --> 00:09:28,629
Am I going to get sued?

145
00:09:28,629 --> 00:09:30,396
Ah, would he really go that far?

146
00:09:30,396 --> 00:09:34,396
Ah, who knew I'd run into my boss there?

147
00:09:34,396 --> 00:09:37,662
True, thinking about seeing
them at work... ugh!

148
00:09:37,662 --> 00:09:38,929
Seriously creepy.

149
00:09:38,929 --> 00:09:41,262
I didn't want Team Leader Bang to see me,

150
00:09:41,262 --> 00:09:45,396
so I pulled all kinds of stunts
with a total stranger.

151
00:09:45,396 --> 00:09:48,562
Does he really think I've lost my mind?

152
00:09:48,562 --> 00:09:51,662
Yeah, the odds are definitely high.

153
00:09:51,662 --> 00:09:53,829
But what does he look like? Handsome?

154
00:09:53,829 --> 00:09:56,496
I don't know. He had sunglasses on,
couldn't really see.

155
00:09:56,496 --> 00:09:57,996
Ah, what a waste.

156
00:09:57,996 --> 00:10:01,062
It's not about getting splashed
by grape juice. You should've locked eyes.

157
00:10:01,062 --> 00:10:02,662
Oh, what are you saying?

158
00:10:02,662 --> 00:10:03,662
Oh gosh,

159
00:10:03,662 --> 00:10:05,229
here comes Miss Prim again.

160
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:06,396
From what I see,

161
00:10:06,396 --> 00:10:08,762
your rigid walls ruined an entire
truckload of potential romance.

162
00:10:08,762 --> 00:10:11,621
Hey, what walls did I even put up?

163
00:10:11,621 --> 00:10:13,696
Hey, don't you remember?

164
00:10:16,953 --> 00:10:19,237
[Ten years ago]

165
00:10:34,996 --> 00:10:36,429
- Why? What?
- Oh my.

166
00:10:36,429 --> 00:10:39,762
- What are you touching right now?
- Oh, hey.

167
00:10:39,762 --> 00:10:44,196
Every guy who tried flirting
with you eventually gave up.

168
00:10:44,196 --> 00:10:47,596
That's because they tried
to rush things way too fast.

169
00:10:47,596 --> 00:10:49,986
Hui Won, you need to
drop that old-fashioned idea

170
00:10:49,986 --> 00:10:51,329
that you must 'take it slow'

171
00:10:51,329 --> 00:10:53,129
when seeing someone.

172
00:10:53,129 --> 00:10:54,562
If the vibe's right,

173
00:10:54,562 --> 00:10:56,421
you can get everything done

174
00:10:56,421 --> 00:10:58,062
in half a day.

175
00:10:58,062 --> 00:11:00,229
Hey.

176
00:11:00,229 --> 00:11:04,496
You're only against marriage,
not dating, right?

177
00:11:04,496 --> 00:11:07,396
Of course, I'll date.

178
00:11:07,396 --> 00:11:09,062
I even have someone I like.

179
00:11:09,062 --> 00:11:12,029
Oh you? Who?

180
00:11:12,029 --> 00:11:15,229
There is. Don't be surprised later
when you see how handsome he is.

181
00:11:15,229 --> 00:11:16,929
Alrighty then, okay.

182
00:11:16,929 --> 00:11:18,829
Drink up. Let's drink ourselves
to death tonight.

183
00:11:18,829 --> 00:11:20,962
Hey, you're paying for everything
here tonight, okay?

184
00:11:20,962 --> 00:11:22,562
Cheers!

185
00:11:22,562 --> 00:11:24,517
Ah, this is so funny.

186
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,029
Oh.

187
00:11:26,029 --> 00:11:28,929
I had such a rough day today, seriously.

188
00:11:32,862 --> 00:11:34,262
Sir, give me a bottle of Try...

189
00:11:34,262 --> 00:11:36,129
No, no, make it two bottles, please.

190
00:11:39,196 --> 00:11:40,362
Cheers.

191
00:11:40,362 --> 00:11:43,796
- You're going down tonight.
- I'm gonna beat you today.

192
00:11:45,829 --> 00:11:48,329
- No sipping!
- I finished it all.

193
00:11:52,796 --> 00:11:55,129
Sad?

194
00:11:55,845 --> 00:11:57,296
Huh? I'm not drunk.

195
00:11:57,296 --> 00:11:59,396
- You know, I'm usually super cool, right?
- It's not that, seriously.

196
00:11:59,396 --> 00:12:01,562
- Three, six, nine. Three, six, nine!
- Bang!

197
00:12:06,262 --> 00:12:08,329
Drunk?

198
00:12:08,329 --> 00:12:10,296
Wake up. Time for round two.

199
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:13,029
Sir, another bottle of Try here, please.

200
00:12:13,029 --> 00:12:16,562
So then, he suddenly disappeared?

201
00:12:21,962 --> 00:12:23,729
Got it for now.

202
00:12:26,529 --> 00:12:28,429
Oh, my head...

203
00:12:29,562 --> 00:12:31,029
See?

204
00:12:31,029 --> 00:12:33,096
I told you I should go keep an eye on him.

205
00:12:33,096 --> 00:12:35,096
You know that blind date the other day?

206
00:12:35,096 --> 00:12:38,829
He set Chae Yeon's childhood pictures
as his phone wallpaper

207
00:12:38,829 --> 00:12:42,462
and even pretended to be her father.

208
00:12:42,462 --> 00:12:43,629
Oh, my head...

209
00:12:43,629 --> 00:12:45,762
I had to explain that mess...

210
00:12:45,762 --> 00:12:49,696
He's that desperate not to get married,
so let's give him some time.

211
00:12:49,696 --> 00:12:52,362
You calm down too.
Jeong Eum will be here soon.

212
00:12:52,362 --> 00:12:54,229
How could I possibly calm down?

213
00:12:54,229 --> 00:12:55,729
Do you think I don't know

214
00:12:55,729 --> 00:12:58,062
how the board's been itching to tear

215
00:12:58,062 --> 00:13:01,196
Du Jun apart ever since your sabbatical?

216
00:13:01,196 --> 00:13:03,362
- I'll try to handle that...
- Oh, dear.

217
00:13:03,362 --> 00:13:05,096
How exactly?

218
00:13:05,096 --> 00:13:09,029
Like last time, when everything blew up,
and you only showed up to clean the mess?

219
00:13:09,029 --> 00:13:12,262
He's not acting this way for no reason.

220
00:13:12,262 --> 00:13:15,562
It's that pointless
sense of responsibility of his.

221
00:13:15,562 --> 00:13:18,162
From what I see, Jeong Eum must be

222
00:13:18,162 --> 00:13:19,896
pressuring Du Jun somehow...

223
00:13:19,896 --> 00:13:21,662
Pressuring him how?

224
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:26,396
Oh? You're here.

225
00:13:26,396 --> 00:13:28,362
Sit here.

226
00:13:28,362 --> 00:13:30,396
Se Hyeon has plans?

227
00:13:30,396 --> 00:13:31,396
Yes.

228
00:13:31,396 --> 00:13:32,762
Oh.

229
00:13:32,762 --> 00:13:34,562
Let's continue the conversation
you two were having.

230
00:13:34,562 --> 00:13:36,357
I love talking about myself.

231
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,200
Oh.

232
00:13:38,896 --> 00:13:40,729
Well, since Du Jun

233
00:13:40,729 --> 00:13:45,229
keeps avoiding blind dates
and refuses to get married...

234
00:13:45,229 --> 00:13:48,062
Is marriage really necessary?

235
00:13:48,062 --> 00:13:51,096
It's not like marriage guarantees
you won't end up alone.

236
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:52,829
Just like me.

237
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:00,362
Excuse me for a moment.

238
00:14:01,662 --> 00:14:04,662
Yeah, I'm with my in-laws.

239
00:14:05,729 --> 00:14:07,796
Mr. Lee?

240
00:14:09,429 --> 00:14:12,329
Has that punk lost his mind?

241
00:14:15,329 --> 00:14:16,696
Tell him to get out.

242
00:14:16,696 --> 00:14:19,796
Show him what happens
when he stabs me in the back.

243
00:14:24,896 --> 00:14:26,129
Sorry, it's work-related.

244
00:14:26,129 --> 00:14:29,062
Oh, yes.

245
00:14:29,696 --> 00:14:31,396
It's okay.

246
00:15:01,929 --> 00:15:04,962
But seriously, why don't you
want to get married?

247
00:15:04,962 --> 00:15:06,296
I can't.

248
00:15:06,296 --> 00:15:08,596
I said I can't do it.

249
00:15:10,008 --> 00:15:13,560
No! No!

250
00:15:14,362 --> 00:15:18,162
How could I dare think of marriage,
after destroying a family with my own hands?

251
00:15:49,337 --> 00:15:50,597
[Beer]

252
00:15:52,005 --> 00:15:53,029
[It's Beer Time]

253
00:15:58,196 --> 00:15:59,462
Fourteen bottles of beer?

254
00:15:59,462 --> 00:16:03,229
See? She didn't become
the youngest manager for nothing.

255
00:16:03,229 --> 00:16:05,196
What, did she even brag about proving it?

256
00:16:05,196 --> 00:16:07,096
Even without that, the Germany slot
is obviously Manager Jang's.

257
00:16:07,096 --> 00:16:08,129
Germany?

258
00:16:08,129 --> 00:16:09,496
Guess you haven't heard, Se Hyeon.

259
00:16:09,496 --> 00:16:12,796
Every three years, the company
picks top-performing employees

260
00:16:12,796 --> 00:16:14,229
for a study program in Germany.

261
00:16:14,229 --> 00:16:16,896
But competition's insane these days,

262
00:16:16,896 --> 00:16:18,662
so rumor is they're even
scoring creativity now.

263
00:16:18,662 --> 00:16:20,996
Still, who could possibly beat Manager Jang?

264
00:16:20,996 --> 00:16:25,629
I've never seen anyone so relentless
in new product development.

265
00:16:25,629 --> 00:16:28,862
She heard minerals were
used in medicine and cosmetics

266
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:31,829
and went mining for ones
that could work in beer.

267
00:16:31,829 --> 00:16:34,629
That's not all. She planned
limited-edition beer with rare fruit

268
00:16:34,629 --> 00:16:36,029
and went trekking through jungles.

269
00:16:36,029 --> 00:16:37,996
Wow, is she some kind of Tarzan?

270
00:16:37,996 --> 00:16:41,096
Last month, for some special Himalayan yeast,

271
00:16:41,096 --> 00:16:42,229
she was scaling ice walls...

272
00:16:42,229 --> 00:16:44,429
Manager Nam In Nam?

273
00:16:44,429 --> 00:16:45,862
You went around calling me
Tarzan again, didn't you?

274
00:16:45,862 --> 00:16:48,896
Because of you, there are all
these weird rumors going around.

275
00:16:48,896 --> 00:16:50,529
Did I say anything that wasn't true?

276
00:16:50,529 --> 00:16:52,729
Just exaggerated a tiny bit.

277
00:16:52,729 --> 00:16:55,596
A tiny bit? About...

278
00:16:55,596 --> 00:16:57,062
- 70%?
- Assistant Manager Choi.

279
00:16:57,062 --> 00:16:58,362
It just shows Manager Jang's

280
00:16:58,362 --> 00:17:00,729
unmatched role
in our New Product Development Team.

281
00:17:00,729 --> 00:17:02,962
Our ace.

282
00:17:02,962 --> 00:17:04,997
Absolutely, you are my role model.

283
00:17:04,997 --> 00:17:06,661
I'm telling the truth.

284
00:17:06,661 --> 00:17:09,262
- Hey quiet now.
- Shut it.

285
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:11,462
What? Why did everyone
suddenly stop laughing?

286
00:17:11,462 --> 00:17:13,029
Conference room. Now.

287
00:17:13,029 --> 00:17:15,029
No ideas at all?

288
00:17:15,029 --> 00:17:16,229
You, intern.

289
00:17:16,229 --> 00:17:18,462
- Yes?
- Got any brilliant ideas?

290
00:17:18,462 --> 00:17:20,696
They say Gen Z these days
come up with fresh, creative ideas,

291
00:17:20,696 --> 00:17:23,529
but I guess not all of them do.

292
00:17:25,729 --> 00:17:27,829
You must've learned something in a month.

293
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:29,529
Didn't your supervisor teach you anything?

294
00:17:29,529 --> 00:17:31,029
Just scold me already.

295
00:17:31,029 --> 00:17:32,729
I think that's what you wanted to say to me.

296
00:17:32,729 --> 00:17:35,196
Fine, you talk well.

297
00:17:35,196 --> 00:17:36,562
Now, show me what you've got.

298
00:17:36,562 --> 00:17:39,062
Set an example as a senior.

299
00:17:40,596 --> 00:17:44,096
You think you can just sit back
now that Germany's basically a done deal?

300
00:17:44,096 --> 00:17:48,896
I suppose that's smarter than getting
involved and docking your own score.

301
00:17:53,062 --> 00:17:55,296
So, I just need to bring it
by the next meeting, right?

302
00:17:55,296 --> 00:17:59,196
A groundbreaking idea to boost beer sales?

303
00:18:01,862 --> 00:18:03,796
So, you went head-to-head
with your boss again?

304
00:18:03,796 --> 00:18:07,929
I worked all weekend because of her,
and now she's messing with my junior.

305
00:18:07,929 --> 00:18:10,162
Why's she always obsessed
with taking me down?

306
00:18:10,162 --> 00:18:14,262
Because a junior who's better
than her keeps threatening her turf.

307
00:18:14,262 --> 00:18:17,129
She blames you for last year's
failed promotion, right?

308
00:18:17,129 --> 00:18:18,496
No, that was

309
00:18:18,496 --> 00:18:21,796
because she tried to claim
our team's all-nighter as her work.

310
00:18:21,796 --> 00:18:25,129
Anyway, I stormed out in anger earlier,

311
00:18:25,129 --> 00:18:28,596
but where do I find such an idea?

312
00:18:28,596 --> 00:18:30,496
Took a while to find.

313
00:19:07,296 --> 00:19:11,462
You were a handful in middle school,
and you still are.

314
00:19:17,462 --> 00:19:19,429
[14 years ago]

315
00:19:19,429 --> 00:19:21,093
[Cha Min Uk]

316
00:19:24,029 --> 00:19:27,329
At this point, you owe your knees an apology.

317
00:19:29,029 --> 00:19:30,696
It hurts.

318
00:19:30,696 --> 00:19:32,396
Stop whining.

319
00:19:53,796 --> 00:19:55,529
Here too.

320
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,562
Are you okay?

321
00:20:30,196 --> 00:20:32,462
Had a blind date over the weekend?

322
00:20:32,462 --> 00:20:34,029
Did Mi Ran say that?

323
00:20:34,029 --> 00:20:36,596
No, I was hoping the three of us
could grab a drink after so long.

324
00:20:36,596 --> 00:20:38,796
But she said you have a very important date.

325
00:20:39,429 --> 00:20:42,096
No, it's not that. Not at all.

326
00:20:42,096 --> 00:20:46,562
I thought maybe you'd finally
started thinking about marriage.

327
00:20:46,562 --> 00:20:48,496
You know how my parents are.

328
00:20:48,496 --> 00:20:50,496
Get out! Get out!

329
00:20:50,496 --> 00:20:51,996
Why should I leave? This is my house!

330
00:20:51,996 --> 00:20:53,162
Since when?

331
00:20:53,162 --> 00:20:55,396
How could you do this to us?

332
00:20:55,396 --> 00:20:58,229
Dad, Dad!

333
00:20:58,229 --> 00:21:00,396
Dad, please don't go.

334
00:21:00,396 --> 00:21:03,429
Dad, please don't go.

335
00:21:03,429 --> 00:21:05,796
Dad.

336
00:21:05,796 --> 00:21:08,129
Dad.

337
00:21:09,629 --> 00:21:10,629
Huh?

338
00:21:10,629 --> 00:21:14,362
You still think your parents' divorce
was your fault?

339
00:21:14,362 --> 00:21:16,429
So, why would anyone marry without love?

340
00:21:16,429 --> 00:21:20,062
Even if it hadn't been Dad's affair,
they would've divorced anyway.

341
00:21:20,062 --> 00:21:22,029
They weren't compatible.

342
00:21:22,029 --> 00:21:25,629
When well-matched people meet,
they might go a lifetime without fighting.

343
00:21:25,629 --> 00:21:26,729
Then, you...

344
00:21:26,729 --> 00:21:30,796
Even if you meet someone
you truly love later, you won't marry?

345
00:21:30,796 --> 00:21:31,796
Huh?

346
00:21:31,796 --> 00:21:32,862
Never mind.

347
00:21:32,862 --> 00:21:36,662
Why am I asking so much
to someone who prioritizes work?

348
00:21:41,496 --> 00:21:43,762
I should go. The team leader called for me.

349
00:21:43,762 --> 00:21:47,529
Ah, what? You said you'd help me
figure out the beer issue.

350
00:21:49,296 --> 00:21:50,929
Don't overthink it.

351
00:21:50,929 --> 00:21:54,196
Being overly cautious can be poison.

352
00:21:54,196 --> 00:21:57,229
The path lies where you seek the answer.

353
00:21:57,229 --> 00:21:59,929
Beer problems get solved at a pub.

354
00:21:59,929 --> 00:22:01,362
I'll get going.

355
00:22:01,362 --> 00:22:03,562
Hey.

356
00:22:03,562 --> 00:22:05,262
I really have to go.

357
00:22:12,029 --> 00:22:15,062
I became more careful because of you...

358
00:22:22,917 --> 00:22:24,837
Oh.

359
00:22:26,629 --> 00:22:27,973
What brings you here?

360
00:22:27,973 --> 00:22:29,529
Hey.

361
00:22:29,529 --> 00:22:31,696
Say hello to him.

362
00:22:31,696 --> 00:22:33,862
This is Manager Song, a good friend of mine.

363
00:22:33,862 --> 00:22:36,762
Pleased to meet you. I'm Manager Song.

364
00:22:41,196 --> 00:22:44,517
Apologies, but I need to step out.
Please get straight to the point.

365
00:22:44,517 --> 00:22:45,925
Huh?

366
00:22:45,925 --> 00:22:49,162
Oh.

367
00:22:49,162 --> 00:22:53,662
You remember the commercial
building project I mentioned before?

368
00:22:53,662 --> 00:22:56,462
I was thinking of doing that
together with Manager Song.

369
00:22:56,462 --> 00:22:58,129
I believe I addressed that last time.

370
00:22:58,129 --> 00:22:59,629
There's already a qualified person for that.

371
00:22:59,629 --> 00:23:04,962
More importantly, Q2 operating profits
for the resort business hit a historic low.

372
00:23:04,962 --> 00:23:07,396
With your approval, Vice Chairman,
I'll reassign the lead.

373
00:23:07,396 --> 00:23:09,629
Are you saying you'll fire Team Leader Park?

374
00:23:09,629 --> 00:23:13,362
More like relocating the team
to a suitable position.

375
00:23:13,362 --> 00:23:15,062
No, but still...

376
00:23:15,062 --> 00:23:18,829
Team Leader Park has handled
the resort project since the beginning...

377
00:23:18,829 --> 00:23:21,262
Compensation is repaid with results.

378
00:23:21,262 --> 00:23:22,729
Not loyalty or diligence.

379
00:23:22,729 --> 00:23:24,962
If there's nothing else, I'll take my leave.

380
00:23:24,962 --> 00:23:26,696
I have a meeting.

381
00:23:30,329 --> 00:23:32,996
That insolent little...

382
00:23:43,262 --> 00:23:45,062
That's right, that's right.

383
00:23:45,062 --> 00:23:46,962
Oh, yeah.

384
00:23:49,696 --> 00:23:51,262
Oh, you're here.

385
00:23:51,262 --> 00:23:52,462
Doing this at the office too?

386
00:23:52,462 --> 00:23:53,762
Wrong question.

387
00:23:53,762 --> 00:23:55,596
I can only do this at work.

388
00:23:55,596 --> 00:23:57,996
Your mom would smack my back if she saw this.

389
00:23:57,996 --> 00:23:59,662
That's right, that's right.

390
00:23:59,662 --> 00:24:01,329
Mom's still really mad, huh?

391
00:24:01,329 --> 00:24:03,996
She's always been like that.

392
00:24:03,996 --> 00:24:06,062
[Finish]
That's right, yay!

393
00:24:06,062 --> 00:24:07,896
[Mari]
I came in first place.

394
00:24:07,896 --> 00:24:10,929
This game's great for relieving stress.

395
00:24:13,529 --> 00:24:15,462
Still busy these days?

396
00:24:15,462 --> 00:24:17,529
Rumor has it you're working like a warrior.

397
00:24:17,529 --> 00:24:20,029
I'm just doing what needs to be done.

398
00:24:24,929 --> 00:24:26,829
That gesture with your hand...

399
00:24:29,396 --> 00:24:30,629
Never mind.

400
00:24:30,629 --> 00:24:33,562
Ah, Du Jun, first you need
recognition from the board.

401
00:24:33,562 --> 00:24:36,896
It seems Moo Young is trying
to shake up the board with this issue.

402
00:24:36,896 --> 00:24:39,162
Now, hand over
the trading company affairs to me.

403
00:24:39,162 --> 00:24:40,762
- Father.
- Instead, from now on,

404
00:24:40,762 --> 00:24:43,529
you report to Taehan Liquor.

405
00:24:44,696 --> 00:24:47,429
As president, not managing director.

406
00:24:54,229 --> 00:24:58,529
With spicy greasy food, lagers
completely lose their flavor and aroma.

407
00:24:58,529 --> 00:25:00,029
'You're better off with something aromatic.'

408
00:25:00,029 --> 00:25:02,196
'Stout works well, IPA's fine too.'

409
00:25:02,196 --> 00:25:04,696
I want to tell them that.

410
00:25:04,696 --> 00:25:06,596
But I should hold back, right?

411
00:25:09,896 --> 00:25:11,429
Do you know him?

412
00:25:11,429 --> 00:25:14,996
Huh? No, nothing.

413
00:25:14,996 --> 00:25:15,996
Boyfriend?

414
00:25:15,996 --> 00:25:18,596
Ugh, your face turned bright red.

415
00:25:18,596 --> 00:25:20,762
He's a bit older, but a total romantic.

416
00:25:20,762 --> 00:25:24,862
Though whether it's 3 months or 30 years,
we'll have to live together to find out.

417
00:25:24,862 --> 00:25:26,829
Live together?

418
00:25:26,829 --> 00:25:30,596
Cohabitation. I firmly believe in
living together before marriage.

419
00:25:30,596 --> 00:25:32,029
Well, true.

420
00:25:32,029 --> 00:25:34,462
Breaking up is better than getting divorced.

421
00:25:34,462 --> 00:25:36,696
You have a boyfriend, right, Manager?

422
00:25:36,696 --> 00:25:39,096
Someone this perfect
can't possibly be single.

423
00:25:39,096 --> 00:25:40,196
I'm dying to know.

424
00:25:40,196 --> 00:25:42,629
What kind of unicorn is your boyfriend?

425
00:25:42,629 --> 00:25:43,996
Unicorn?

426
00:25:43,996 --> 00:25:47,729
Makes sense. I've never seen him.

427
00:25:48,496 --> 00:25:50,162
Let's drink. Drink.

428
00:25:50,162 --> 00:25:51,762
Here.

429
00:25:51,762 --> 00:25:53,462
Cheers!

430
00:25:59,813 --> 00:26:03,396
[Min Uk]

431
00:26:03,396 --> 00:26:06,596
Did you get off work? Have you eaten?

432
00:26:15,162 --> 00:26:16,229
I'm dying to know.

433
00:26:16,229 --> 00:26:18,429
What kind of unicorn is your boyfriend?

434
00:26:18,429 --> 00:26:22,029
When well-matched people meet,
they might go a lifetime without fighting.

435
00:26:22,029 --> 00:26:27,096
Even if you meet someone
you truly love later, you won't marry?

436
00:26:27,096 --> 00:26:29,862
Yeah, someone like Min Uk would be fine.

437
00:26:29,862 --> 00:26:31,796
Ugh, what am I even thinking right now?

438
00:26:31,796 --> 00:26:33,629
Get a grip.

439
00:26:40,929 --> 00:26:46,277
[Did you get off work? Have you eaten?]

440
00:26:47,962 --> 00:26:50,162
He should be off work by now.

441
00:26:50,162 --> 00:26:52,062
Did he pass out from exhaustion?

442
00:26:59,929 --> 00:27:03,696
I even bought tteokbokki
from his favorite spot.

443
00:27:03,696 --> 00:27:05,362
But he's not answering.

444
00:27:05,362 --> 00:27:07,829
It's only good for Hwang Mi Ran, then.

445
00:27:11,062 --> 00:27:13,296
Why is she out there?

446
00:27:16,596 --> 00:27:18,362
Cha Min Uk?

447
00:28:04,229 --> 00:28:06,117
I told you about her, right? It's Mi Ran.

448
00:28:06,117 --> 00:28:08,362
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

449
00:28:08,362 --> 00:28:10,129
I even have someone I like.

450
00:28:10,129 --> 00:28:11,496
Oh you? Who?

451
00:28:24,829 --> 00:28:26,196
You report to Taehan Liquor.

452
00:28:26,196 --> 00:28:28,229
As president, not managing director.

453
00:28:40,165 --> 00:28:42,162
Oh, no.

454
00:28:42,162 --> 00:28:46,296
Why did it have to spill out like this?

455
00:29:10,862 --> 00:29:12,965
[Chapter 4 Fate]

456
00:29:15,762 --> 00:29:17,093
What?

457
00:29:19,173 --> 00:29:21,093
Darn it.

458
00:29:26,229 --> 00:29:27,329
Hey!

459
00:29:27,329 --> 00:29:29,696
Come out here, please!

460
00:29:29,696 --> 00:29:33,396
How could you do this to me, huh?

461
00:29:33,396 --> 00:29:35,629
What did I do wrong?

462
00:29:35,629 --> 00:29:39,129
Why are you treating me like this?

463
00:29:40,796 --> 00:29:42,996
What? Is she drunk?

464
00:29:44,129 --> 00:29:45,796
I'm sorry.

465
00:29:45,796 --> 00:29:47,596
I'll compensate you however much you want.

466
00:29:47,596 --> 00:29:50,729
You could've at least given me a heads-up.

467
00:29:50,729 --> 00:29:54,562
How could you stab me in the back like this?

468
00:29:56,562 --> 00:29:58,762
What's wrong with her?

469
00:30:01,596 --> 00:30:03,462
I'm sorry.

470
00:30:03,462 --> 00:30:05,196
Hey there.

471
00:30:05,862 --> 00:30:08,096
Why is your tint so dark?

472
00:30:09,462 --> 00:30:11,762
Hey! Hey!

473
00:30:11,762 --> 00:30:14,196
What are you doing in there?

474
00:30:15,362 --> 00:30:17,096
Hey!

475
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:24,829
Hey! Don't you dare drive away!

476
00:30:24,829 --> 00:30:26,629
That crazy...

477
00:30:26,629 --> 00:30:28,613
[Check: One million won]
Jeez.

478
00:30:31,429 --> 00:30:34,529
Is... he an angel?

479
00:30:35,862 --> 00:30:40,629
Suddenly telling me to buy
every type of beer? What now?

480
00:30:40,629 --> 00:30:41,929
Whew, almost had a disaster today.

481
00:30:41,929 --> 00:30:44,296
Goodness, is our director
going through puberty?

482
00:30:44,296 --> 00:30:45,462
You're drinking beer
you normally wouldn't touch...

483
00:30:45,462 --> 00:30:46,862
You just decided to run wild?

484
00:30:46,862 --> 00:30:49,796
What are you talking about?
I was holding back before.

485
00:30:49,796 --> 00:30:51,362
And now?

486
00:30:51,362 --> 00:30:53,329
Because I need it now.

487
00:30:54,162 --> 00:30:57,596
Have you ever had a drink with me
besides during study abroad?

488
00:30:57,596 --> 00:31:01,296
Back then, I felt sorry for you
whining about having no friends.

489
00:31:01,296 --> 00:31:03,796
Anyway, as of today, I'm stepping back from
the foundation and trading company.

490
00:31:03,796 --> 00:31:04,962
What?

491
00:31:04,962 --> 00:31:07,462
Once the handover is done, I'll
start at Taehan Liquor immediately.

492
00:31:07,462 --> 00:31:09,729
No, wait. Suddenly?

493
00:31:09,729 --> 00:31:13,262
Giving up something good
for gossip-filled Taehan Liquor...

494
00:31:14,229 --> 00:31:15,862
Demand it confidently from the chairman.

495
00:31:15,862 --> 00:31:18,496
Tell him you have something
you want to do! A dream!

496
00:31:18,496 --> 00:31:20,262
Do I even have something like that?

497
00:31:20,262 --> 00:31:23,696
Anyway, schedule me for
all liquor-related events going forward.

498
00:31:23,696 --> 00:31:27,796
And make sure to clip every article
about competitors, got it?

499
00:31:28,729 --> 00:31:31,962
- Got it.
- Why drink before finishing the work?

500
00:31:35,229 --> 00:31:36,929
Huh?

501
00:31:57,862 --> 00:31:59,662
What?

502
00:32:00,829 --> 00:32:02,596
Just go.

503
00:32:14,277 --> 00:32:16,529
Darn, I really want a drink.

504
00:32:21,396 --> 00:32:23,362
I'm sending you because
you said you wanted a drink.

505
00:32:23,362 --> 00:32:25,929
You know that Yellow beer launched in Korea?

506
00:32:25,929 --> 00:32:29,196
The party's there today,
at the flagship store in Itaewon.

507
00:32:29,196 --> 00:32:33,445
Just make a good impression
and capture the vibe of the place.

508
00:32:33,445 --> 00:32:34,917
Come on!

509
00:32:50,053 --> 00:32:51,621
[Yellow Beer]

510
00:32:56,629 --> 00:32:58,629
Perfect timing.

511
00:32:58,629 --> 00:33:00,796
I was craving a drink.

512
00:33:00,796 --> 00:33:02,529
Ta-da!

513
00:33:04,029 --> 00:33:08,529
Ah, mixing it like that ruins the flavor.

514
00:33:09,229 --> 00:33:10,862
Jang Hui Won, calm down.

515
00:33:10,862 --> 00:33:15,896
Just drink quietly and don't meddle today.

516
00:33:15,896 --> 00:33:17,596
Calm down.

517
00:33:22,996 --> 00:33:26,462
Drink, drink, drink.

518
00:33:26,462 --> 00:33:28,262
Take it easy. Are you here to party?

519
00:33:28,262 --> 00:33:30,962
So Du Jun's here to study, huh?

520
00:33:30,962 --> 00:33:32,296
You go home first.

521
00:33:32,296 --> 00:33:34,062
I'm not going home today.

522
00:33:34,062 --> 00:33:36,662
No, I can't go home. I can't.

523
00:33:36,662 --> 00:33:39,296
Want me to ban you from the office too?

524
00:33:42,462 --> 00:33:44,829
Don't look at me like that.

525
00:33:44,829 --> 00:33:47,496
I'm so stressed. Just seeing your face...

526
00:33:47,496 --> 00:33:49,462
Don't you know I have a sensitive stomach?

527
00:33:49,462 --> 00:33:51,262
I really have stomach trouble...

528
00:33:52,496 --> 00:33:54,129
I've got the signal...
Gotta run to the bathroom.

529
00:33:54,129 --> 00:33:56,029
- Here we go again.
- Jeez.

530
00:33:56,029 --> 00:33:58,062
Bathroom! Bathroom!

531
00:34:00,762 --> 00:34:03,896
Jeez, I should really need to
handle things alone next time.

532
00:34:12,862 --> 00:34:14,662
Why does it taste like this?

533
00:34:20,429 --> 00:34:22,562
Wait, that woman...

534
00:34:26,929 --> 00:34:28,729
That crazy woman from back then.

535
00:34:28,729 --> 00:34:30,629
Oh no, I could get in trouble.

536
00:34:31,862 --> 00:34:34,262
- You scared me!
- What now, again?

537
00:34:34,262 --> 00:34:36,862
Again? Do you know me?

538
00:34:36,862 --> 00:34:39,296
No, I absolutely don't know you.

539
00:34:40,629 --> 00:34:44,296
But isn't this a bit much?

540
00:34:44,296 --> 00:34:46,029
What do you mean?

541
00:34:58,129 --> 00:35:00,329
When pouring wheat beer,

542
00:35:00,329 --> 00:35:04,696
tilt the glass at 45 degrees
and fill only 70%.

543
00:35:05,429 --> 00:35:06,693
Then,

544
00:35:06,693 --> 00:35:08,183
[Yeast]
you should pour in the rest

545
00:35:08,183 --> 00:35:09,629
including the settled yeast

546
00:35:09,629 --> 00:35:12,062
to deepen the flavor.

547
00:35:35,462 --> 00:35:37,541
Finish it

548
00:35:37,541 --> 00:35:39,262
with this caramel popcorn.

549
00:35:39,262 --> 00:35:43,262
The sweet-salty combo
will balance the subtle bitterness.

550
00:35:54,996 --> 00:35:56,729
How is it?

551
00:36:01,929 --> 00:36:04,462
I'll take my leave then.

552
00:36:04,462 --> 00:36:07,596
Are you some kind of
beer expert or something?

553
00:36:07,596 --> 00:36:09,162
Pardon?

554
00:36:09,162 --> 00:36:11,129
I want to know more.

555
00:36:18,896 --> 00:36:19,996
[Stout, Dark Chocolate]

556
00:36:19,996 --> 00:36:20,996
[Wheat Beer, Churros]

557
00:36:20,996 --> 00:36:22,405
[IPA, Chicken Wings; Lager, Sausage]

558
00:36:43,596 --> 00:36:45,496
So, how was my recommendation?

559
00:36:45,496 --> 00:36:48,696
My nickname is Beer Master!

560
00:36:48,696 --> 00:36:49,796
No, no, no.

561
00:36:49,796 --> 00:36:52,262
Beer Legend!

562
00:36:52,262 --> 00:36:54,277
Not sure about legend...

563
00:36:54,277 --> 00:36:56,037
Hey!

564
00:36:57,996 --> 00:37:00,662
But isn't this way too much?

565
00:37:00,662 --> 00:37:04,229
Ah, this is nothing.

566
00:37:11,045 --> 00:37:16,329
Now, the current high score is 340 points!

567
00:37:17,096 --> 00:37:20,162
Any more participants
for the basketball game?

568
00:37:20,162 --> 00:37:22,362
The prizes include

569
00:37:22,362 --> 00:37:24,729
a premium home-brew beer maker

570
00:37:24,729 --> 00:37:26,629
and a Love It doll.

571
00:37:26,629 --> 00:37:28,462
Here you are, come on out, come on out.

572
00:37:28,462 --> 00:37:29,762
A craft beer brewing machine.

573
00:37:29,762 --> 00:37:31,429
I really want that.

574
00:37:31,429 --> 00:37:34,062
- Shall I buy you one?
- Oh, never mind.

575
00:37:34,062 --> 00:37:36,762
- No need to buy me one.
- Anyone coming?

576
00:37:36,762 --> 00:37:39,396
Then, why not give it a shot?

577
00:37:40,596 --> 00:37:41,962
Give it a shot? No way...

578
00:37:41,962 --> 00:37:44,496
With your height, I bet you're
good at basketball.

579
00:37:44,496 --> 00:37:46,496
Why do you push so hard?

580
00:37:50,021 --> 00:37:51,621
Jeez.

581
00:37:53,477 --> 00:37:56,196
Ah, this is too...

582
00:37:57,125 --> 00:37:58,821
Oh no.

583
00:38:01,253 --> 00:38:05,221
Oh no, this is too much!

584
00:38:06,462 --> 00:38:10,096
Three, two, one!

585
00:38:11,396 --> 00:38:13,296
So close. Oh, no.

586
00:38:13,296 --> 00:38:15,996
- It's okay!
- It's okay!

587
00:38:15,996 --> 00:38:18,429
Any other challengers?

588
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,429
Here.

589
00:38:20,429 --> 00:38:23,029
Today's final challenger.

590
00:38:23,029 --> 00:38:26,762
Can he actually surpass 340 points?

591
00:38:26,762 --> 00:38:28,996
Are you confident?

592
00:38:28,996 --> 00:38:31,429
Not confident, but I'll try.

593
00:38:31,429 --> 00:38:33,496
What's that supposed to mean?

594
00:38:33,496 --> 00:38:35,696
'No confidence, but I'll try?'

595
00:38:35,696 --> 00:38:37,662
Amazing confidence. Let's see.

596
00:38:37,662 --> 00:38:40,462
He's got an actor's face.

597
00:38:40,462 --> 00:38:41,629
Alright, let's start.

598
00:38:41,629 --> 00:38:43,662
340 points.

599
00:38:43,662 --> 00:38:45,562
Starting now.

600
00:38:45,562 --> 00:38:48,762
I'm nervous.

601
00:38:48,762 --> 00:38:52,596
Why's he taking his jacket off
for basketball?

602
00:38:52,596 --> 00:38:55,396
It's just uncomfortable.

603
00:38:55,396 --> 00:38:57,196
Now, we're extremely uncomfortable too.

604
00:38:57,196 --> 00:39:00,329
Why roll up sleeves now?

605
00:39:00,329 --> 00:39:02,262
- It's just a basketball game...
- Also uncomfortable.

606
00:39:02,262 --> 00:39:05,596
Uncomfortable? Seriously?
You're making everyone uncomfortable.

607
00:39:05,596 --> 00:39:07,729
If you don't beat 340 after this,

608
00:39:07,729 --> 00:39:10,696
it'll be truly awkward.

609
00:39:10,696 --> 00:39:12,429
Cool.

610
00:39:13,996 --> 00:39:16,696
- Go for it!
- Let's start.

611
00:39:17,797 --> 00:39:19,045
[Hunt for the Scoring King]

612
00:39:22,821 --> 00:39:25,029
[Highest Score, Time, Total Score]
What?

613
00:39:25,029 --> 00:39:26,729
What?

614
00:39:49,893 --> 00:39:51,237
[Highest Score, Time, Total Score]

615
00:39:53,362 --> 00:39:55,529
Seven seconds left.

616
00:39:59,929 --> 00:40:03,862
[Highest Score, Time, Total Score]
Six, five, four, three,

617
00:40:03,862 --> 00:40:06,929
[Challenge Failed]
two, one.

618
00:40:08,729 --> 00:40:10,462
Yes!

619
00:40:11,162 --> 00:40:12,196
Yes!

620
00:40:12,196 --> 00:40:13,362
- That was close.
- Wait!

621
00:40:13,362 --> 00:40:14,496
They cheated over there.

622
00:40:14,496 --> 00:40:16,129
They just blinded me.

623
00:40:16,129 --> 00:40:17,829
Blinded what?

624
00:40:17,829 --> 00:40:20,096
They used phone flash to blind me.

625
00:40:20,096 --> 00:40:22,229
That's cheating! Fraud!

626
00:40:22,229 --> 00:40:23,296
No, I didn't.

627
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:24,696
Did you blind him with flash?

628
00:40:24,696 --> 00:40:26,096
No, no, not at all.

629
00:40:26,096 --> 00:40:27,462
- No.
- Not true.

630
00:40:27,462 --> 00:40:29,996
He doesn't even have a phone!

631
00:40:29,996 --> 00:40:30,996
Handsome guys get away with anything?

632
00:40:30,996 --> 00:40:33,362
[Highest Score 340, Time 0, Total Score 339]
Games are games, and scores are scores.

633
00:40:33,362 --> 00:40:35,129
Machines don't lie.

634
00:40:35,129 --> 00:40:37,429
The one who scored 340

635
00:40:37,429 --> 00:40:39,862
is our winner.

636
00:40:39,862 --> 00:40:40,862
Here's your prize.

637
00:40:40,862 --> 00:40:42,862
I can't just let myself be pushed around.

638
00:40:42,862 --> 00:40:43,896
How fast are you?

639
00:40:43,896 --> 00:40:46,729
- Run on three.
- Wow, it's big.

640
00:40:49,629 --> 00:40:51,962
- Three!
- Oh, wait.

641
00:40:56,862 --> 00:40:58,562
Hurry up.

642
00:41:48,629 --> 00:41:50,562
Ah, so tired.

643
00:41:53,162 --> 00:41:54,596
I can't run anymore.

644
00:41:54,596 --> 00:41:56,562
They're not chasing us now.

645
00:41:58,329 --> 00:42:00,896
But how could you think of
running off with the prize?

646
00:42:00,896 --> 00:42:02,196
It was originally mine anyway.

647
00:42:02,196 --> 00:42:04,329
He's the one who stole it!

648
00:42:05,396 --> 00:42:08,796
But why is this beer maker so light?

649
00:42:08,796 --> 00:42:10,496
- What is this?
- Oh?

650
00:42:16,929 --> 00:42:19,496
You're more clumsy than you look.

651
00:42:19,496 --> 00:42:22,862
Forget it. I let it slide because
your effort was admirable.

652
00:42:23,996 --> 00:42:25,929
Aren't you thirsty?

653
00:42:32,596 --> 00:42:37,096
Anyway, after coming back from the trip,
I kept searching for that flavor.

654
00:42:37,096 --> 00:42:38,962
That's when I made up my mind.

655
00:42:38,962 --> 00:42:41,096
I've decided that I must
study in Germany next.

656
00:42:41,096 --> 00:42:44,762
I've decided to create my own beer
that will captivate foreigners' taste buds.

657
00:42:44,762 --> 00:42:46,762
That's my dream.

658
00:42:47,562 --> 00:42:51,129
You like drinking, have a lot you want to do,

659
00:42:51,129 --> 00:42:53,296
and are full of passion.

660
00:42:53,296 --> 00:42:58,296
I'm passionate, but I lack courage,
so I guess I borrow strength from alcohol.

661
00:42:58,296 --> 00:43:01,562
What about you? What's your dream?

662
00:43:01,562 --> 00:43:03,596
I don't have anything like that.

663
00:43:03,596 --> 00:43:05,229
You don't have anything you want to do?

664
00:43:05,229 --> 00:43:06,996
Do I have to have one?

665
00:43:06,996 --> 00:43:09,296
Just handling my responsibilities
is overwhelming enough.

666
00:43:09,296 --> 00:43:11,296
You live so rigidly.

667
00:43:11,296 --> 00:43:13,829
Are you a perfectionist, something like that?

668
00:43:13,829 --> 00:43:17,596
Well, I guess if a person ever loosens up,
all that happens is mistakes.

669
00:43:17,596 --> 00:43:20,996
How does a person like that
even drink alcohol?

670
00:43:20,996 --> 00:43:23,662
So, I usually don't drink much.

671
00:43:23,662 --> 00:43:27,862
Don't you know this is like an oxygen tank?

672
00:43:27,862 --> 00:43:29,462
Did you know?

673
00:43:29,462 --> 00:43:32,362
Some of the most beloved beers in history

674
00:43:32,362 --> 00:43:35,462
were created by accident or mistake.

675
00:43:35,462 --> 00:43:36,462
This lager

676
00:43:36,462 --> 00:43:42,329
was created by accident
when beer was aged in a cold cave.

677
00:43:42,329 --> 00:43:44,496
If you live too intensely,

678
00:43:44,496 --> 00:43:47,929
you can easily miss
the unexpected moments that come along.

679
00:43:47,929 --> 00:43:49,329
What's so great about having a dream?

680
00:43:49,329 --> 00:43:54,129
Being composed in the face
of mistakes is also a dream.

681
00:44:12,389 --> 00:44:15,429
Then, is this also a mistake?

682
00:45:09,662 --> 00:45:11,589
[Chapter 5 Destiny]

683
00:47:36,562 --> 00:47:38,662
I must be crazy.

684
00:47:58,029 --> 00:48:00,396
Do people usually pay when they leave?

685
00:48:00,396 --> 00:48:02,229
Did I do it when I came in?

686
00:48:02,862 --> 00:48:05,862
If it shows that it's my first time,
it'll be embarrassing.

687
00:48:14,877 --> 00:48:15,877
Right,

688
00:48:15,877 --> 00:48:18,962
[Check: One million won]
this money wasn't really mine from the start.

689
00:48:18,962 --> 00:48:22,129
Goodbye, my money.

690
00:48:37,162 --> 00:48:38,162
What?

691
00:48:38,162 --> 00:48:41,062
Married man? Girlfriend?

692
00:48:55,862 --> 00:48:59,596
Oh my, the ladies are here?

693
00:48:59,596 --> 00:49:03,796
Mrs. Park, I didn't know you were
interested in sponsorship projects like this.

694
00:49:03,796 --> 00:49:07,662
He's sparkling and pretty, isn't he?

695
00:49:08,696 --> 00:49:10,529
Please spread the word a lot.

696
00:49:10,529 --> 00:49:12,229
Say he's an artist with a bright future.

697
00:49:12,229 --> 00:49:14,662
Isn't he the one Taehan Hotel sponsored?

698
00:49:14,662 --> 00:49:15,729
Really?

699
00:49:15,729 --> 00:49:18,896
If President Han finds out,
she won't stay quiet.

700
00:49:18,896 --> 00:49:21,196
Is there anything

701
00:49:21,196 --> 00:49:23,196
money can't solve?

702
00:49:42,562 --> 00:49:44,296
President Han?

703
00:49:46,029 --> 00:49:49,162
Mr. Lee, it's been a while.

704
00:49:49,162 --> 00:49:50,629
You've gotten even prettier
since I last saw you.

705
00:49:50,629 --> 00:49:52,029
Oh, ma'am.

706
00:49:52,029 --> 00:49:56,662
In a world where practicality rules,
loyalty is old-fashioned.

707
00:49:56,662 --> 00:49:59,562
Well done. I'm impressed.

708
00:50:00,529 --> 00:50:01,829
President Han.

709
00:50:01,829 --> 00:50:03,796
Mr. Lee is mine now.

710
00:50:03,796 --> 00:50:06,029
What are you doing, getting all clingy now?

711
00:50:06,029 --> 00:50:08,162
I'm not here to take him away.

712
00:50:08,162 --> 00:50:10,496
I'm not interested in everyone's sweetheart,

713
00:50:10,496 --> 00:50:13,862
but I came to tell you
your calculation is off.

714
00:50:17,296 --> 00:50:19,696
Did you underpay a penalty?

715
00:50:19,696 --> 00:50:21,496
No, no.

716
00:50:26,562 --> 00:50:28,262
President Han!

717
00:50:32,129 --> 00:50:34,629
Now, the calculation is a bit more accurate.

718
00:50:39,296 --> 00:50:41,062
Ugh, my head...

719
00:50:45,529 --> 00:50:47,262
[Check: One million won]
What is this?

720
00:50:51,462 --> 00:50:54,129
This woman is ridiculous.

721
00:50:57,629 --> 00:51:00,662
How can she
just throw the doll away like that?

722
00:51:01,662 --> 00:51:03,596
That's too much.

723
00:51:09,157 --> 00:51:10,341
[Si Hyeong]

724
00:51:11,429 --> 00:51:13,496
- Hey.
- Finally answering.

725
00:51:13,496 --> 00:51:15,929
I thought something happened to you.

726
00:51:15,929 --> 00:51:18,162
- What?
- Do you know how many times I called?

727
00:51:18,162 --> 00:51:20,162
You're a light sleeper.
What on earth happened?

728
00:51:20,162 --> 00:51:22,996
What are you talking about?
I never got any calls...

729
00:51:22,996 --> 00:51:24,562
[Si Hyeong (10)]

730
00:51:24,562 --> 00:51:27,496
What? I slept this deeply?

731
00:51:42,262 --> 00:51:43,929
You said you'd let Mr. Lee go.

732
00:51:43,929 --> 00:51:46,196
- I did let him go.
- But you caused a ruckus.

733
00:51:46,196 --> 00:51:49,496
I said I'd let him go, but I never said
I'd give him away to someone else.

734
00:51:49,496 --> 00:51:50,896
If word gets out about this...

735
00:51:50,896 --> 00:51:52,629
Secretary Yoon.

736
00:51:57,196 --> 00:51:59,096
What brings you here?

737
00:51:59,962 --> 00:52:02,029
Do I have to answer?

738
00:52:02,029 --> 00:52:04,396
You're not here to see me, huh?

739
00:52:06,896 --> 00:52:08,829
Okay, I get what you mean.

740
00:52:11,662 --> 00:52:14,329
Are you sure you have
no plans to get married?

741
00:52:17,962 --> 00:52:21,229
Your mother keeps worrying about you.

742
00:52:21,229 --> 00:52:25,462
But you have no intention to do so at all.

743
00:52:25,462 --> 00:52:26,917
Isn't that right?

744
00:52:26,917 --> 00:52:28,662
[15 years ago]

745
00:52:28,662 --> 00:52:31,696
You ruined my life!

746
00:52:31,696 --> 00:52:33,729
How are you going to take
responsibility for this?

747
00:52:33,729 --> 00:52:35,729
How?

748
00:52:35,729 --> 00:52:38,529
How?

749
00:52:38,529 --> 00:52:40,929
How?

750
00:53:22,596 --> 00:53:25,796
I thought he only worked,
but apparently he does everything.

751
00:53:25,796 --> 00:53:27,562
Find out who was with him.

752
00:53:27,562 --> 00:53:29,296
Yes.

753
00:53:31,996 --> 00:53:33,562
I'm crazy, I'm crazy.

754
00:53:33,562 --> 00:53:36,696
What on earth was I thinking with a stranger?

755
00:53:41,462 --> 00:53:45,029
But that necklace looked
like a gift for a woman.

756
00:53:45,029 --> 00:53:47,296
Could he be married?

757
00:53:47,296 --> 00:53:50,662
Ah, I'm going crazy, I'm losing my mind!

758
00:53:50,662 --> 00:53:52,262
Manager Jang.

759
00:53:52,262 --> 00:53:54,096
Manager Jang.

760
00:53:54,096 --> 00:53:56,796
They say your proposal got approved.

761
00:53:56,796 --> 00:53:59,596
I mean, that logo placement!

762
00:53:59,596 --> 00:54:01,596
According to Manager Jang,
raising the logo placement on the glass

763
00:54:01,596 --> 00:54:04,529
increases the amount of beer and soju poured.

764
00:54:04,529 --> 00:54:07,762
If sales increase,
management won't object much.

765
00:54:07,762 --> 00:54:10,596
First, we'll produce a small batch
with the new print,

766
00:54:10,596 --> 00:54:13,637
and distribute 50 glasses to each partner.

767
00:54:13,637 --> 00:54:15,429
Everyone, get ready.

768
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:20,062
Right, Manager Jang,
finalize the proposal details,

769
00:54:20,062 --> 00:54:22,229
including estimated development costs,
and submit it by next week.

770
00:54:22,229 --> 00:54:23,296
Talk to the procurement team,

771
00:54:23,296 --> 00:54:25,326
and get the schedules
from the beer glass manufacturer

772
00:54:25,326 --> 00:54:26,396
and the printing company too.

773
00:54:26,396 --> 00:54:27,662
Yes.

774
00:54:27,662 --> 00:54:28,829
We'll help too.

775
00:54:28,829 --> 00:54:30,196
Right, just tell us what to do.

776
00:54:30,196 --> 00:54:31,296
Thank you.

777
00:54:31,296 --> 00:54:33,029
Congratulations.

778
00:54:40,429 --> 00:54:42,129
That's when I made up my mind.

779
00:54:42,129 --> 00:54:44,429
I've decided that I must
study in Germany next.

780
00:54:44,429 --> 00:54:48,096
I've decided to create my own beer
that will captivate foreigners' taste buds.

781
00:54:48,096 --> 00:54:50,462
That's my dream.

782
00:55:11,071 --> 00:55:14,693
[Day 1, 2, 3]

783
00:55:21,157 --> 00:55:24,262
[Day 3, 4, 5]

784
00:55:24,262 --> 00:55:28,962
I think it's better to raise it
just this subtly.

785
00:55:29,629 --> 00:55:32,196
We could even name it specifically
for soju-and-beer mixes.

786
00:55:32,196 --> 00:55:33,662
The 'Try' Golden Ratio Glass.

787
00:55:33,662 --> 00:55:35,096
Alright, cheers! Cheers!

788
00:55:35,096 --> 00:55:36,462
Cheers!

789
00:55:36,462 --> 00:55:39,962
[Day 5, 6, 7]
Try!

790
00:55:39,962 --> 00:55:43,129
How is the change
of resort project manager going?

791
00:55:43,129 --> 00:55:46,629
Well, the Vice Chairman said he wants
to give Team Leader Park another chance...

792
00:55:46,629 --> 00:55:50,062
This project is so important to us. Are you
still looking for loyalty over capability?

793
00:55:50,062 --> 00:55:51,962
Find a competent person to handle it,

794
00:55:51,962 --> 00:55:53,896
before I leave.

795
00:55:53,896 --> 00:55:55,962
- Move on, please.
- At the Jeju resort,

796
00:55:55,962 --> 00:56:00,362
they plan to include locally crafted
brewery products in the room packages.

797
00:56:00,362 --> 00:56:01,496
A craft beer brewing machine.

798
00:56:01,496 --> 00:56:03,096
I really want that.

799
00:56:03,096 --> 00:56:04,197
Shall I buy you one?

800
00:56:04,197 --> 00:56:05,733
Hey!

801
00:56:13,729 --> 00:56:15,796
President.

802
00:56:15,796 --> 00:56:17,962
President.

803
00:56:17,962 --> 00:56:21,496
They also plan to release
a separate beer set.

804
00:56:22,296 --> 00:56:23,362
Yes, that sounds good.

805
00:56:23,362 --> 00:56:25,296
It connects with the local community.

806
00:56:25,296 --> 00:56:27,862
Let's extend the duration by about a week.

807
00:56:27,862 --> 00:56:29,829
[Day 7, 8, 9]
Next.

808
00:56:34,229 --> 00:56:37,062
Over here, please put it on the desk.

809
00:56:38,296 --> 00:56:40,029
Thank you.

810
00:56:49,087 --> 00:56:52,837
[Day 9, 10, 11]

811
00:56:59,796 --> 00:57:01,629
When pouring wheat beer,

812
00:57:01,629 --> 00:57:04,929
tilt the glass at 45 degrees
and fill only 70%.

813
00:57:04,929 --> 00:57:08,162
Then, you should pour in the rest
including the settled yeast

814
00:57:08,162 --> 00:57:10,496
to deepen the flavor.

815
00:57:35,167 --> 00:57:38,885
[Day 11, 12, 13]

816
00:57:46,751 --> 00:57:50,533
[Day 13, 14, 15]

817
00:58:09,669 --> 00:58:18,431
[Day 16, 17, 18, 19, 20]

818
00:58:44,729 --> 00:58:46,429
Okay.

819
00:58:50,053 --> 00:58:52,162
- Nice.
- Great!

820
00:58:52,162 --> 00:58:54,196
- It's done.
- Wow.

821
00:58:54,196 --> 00:58:56,196
I knew this would be successful.

822
00:58:56,196 --> 00:58:57,962
- Fine.
- I knew this would be a hit.

823
00:58:57,962 --> 00:58:59,662
Go ahead.

824
00:59:01,029 --> 00:59:04,162
[Pharmacy]

825
00:59:04,162 --> 00:59:05,929
One digestive medicine, please.

826
00:59:05,929 --> 00:59:07,562
What stomach issues are you having?

827
00:59:07,562 --> 00:59:11,196
I'm having indigestion
and feeling a bit nauseous.

828
00:59:11,196 --> 00:59:14,496
My back hurts,
and I'm shivering a little too.

829
00:59:14,496 --> 00:59:16,729
Well... yes.

830
00:59:22,529 --> 00:59:25,562
Could you possibly...

831
00:59:32,562 --> 00:59:33,862
No way.

832
00:59:33,862 --> 00:59:36,196
I'm pregnant?

833
00:59:37,429 --> 00:59:40,329
[5 Years Ago]
It is indeed an endometrial cyst.

834
00:59:40,329 --> 00:59:42,762
Moreover, your uterus is congenitally weak,

835
00:59:42,762 --> 00:59:45,996
so pregnancy might be difficult.

836
00:59:49,462 --> 00:59:51,129
They told me that pregnancy
might be difficult for me.

837
00:59:51,129 --> 00:59:53,096
What is this?

838
00:59:53,096 --> 00:59:54,762
Ah, it hurts.

839
00:59:54,762 --> 00:59:56,862
Hui Won, what are you doing?

840
00:59:56,862 --> 01:00:00,096
Exercise, exercising.

841
01:00:00,096 --> 01:00:01,096
Hurry up, I'm hungry.

842
01:00:01,096 --> 01:00:02,829
Yeah.

843
01:00:04,229 --> 01:00:05,596
Did you think I'd say that?

844
01:00:05,596 --> 01:00:07,329
You're acting weird today.
What is it? What are you hiding?

845
01:00:07,329 --> 01:00:10,096
- It's nothing.
- Got you.

846
01:00:12,129 --> 01:00:14,662
Mi Ran, let me explain first...

847
01:00:14,662 --> 01:00:16,629
Did you have a man?

848
01:00:17,762 --> 01:00:20,996
Last time you said you
liked someone. Is it him?

849
01:00:22,362 --> 01:00:24,362
Tell me quickly, who is it?

850
01:00:24,362 --> 01:00:25,696
Who on earth is he?

851
01:00:25,696 --> 01:00:26,929
Mi Ran, wait a second.

852
01:00:26,929 --> 01:00:29,129
Well, that's...

853
01:00:29,129 --> 01:00:30,896
I don't know who it is.

854
01:00:30,896 --> 01:00:33,062
No, I know who he is.

855
01:00:33,062 --> 01:00:37,596
But I don't know his name or what he does...

856
01:00:38,596 --> 01:00:41,062
What should I do?

857
01:00:41,896 --> 01:00:44,162
You're now five weeks pregnant.

858
01:00:48,696 --> 01:00:51,396
Today, we checked
the gestational sac and yolk sac.

859
01:00:51,396 --> 01:00:54,096
You should be able to hear
the heartbeat around week seven.

860
01:00:54,096 --> 01:00:57,362
It might be slightly delayed
depending on your menstrual cycle.

861
01:00:57,362 --> 01:01:01,062
Shall we schedule your next appointment?

862
01:01:11,029 --> 01:01:14,562
Even now, you're worried about
seeing someone you know?

863
01:01:14,562 --> 01:01:17,062
What did the doctor say?
Are you actually pregnant?

864
01:01:20,496 --> 01:01:22,996
What should I do now?

865
01:01:22,996 --> 01:01:26,629
What do you mean?
You need to find that man first.

866
01:01:26,629 --> 01:01:29,896
Don't you remember anything
about the baby's father?

867
01:01:31,929 --> 01:01:33,096
Well...

868
01:01:33,096 --> 01:01:36,062
He's about 6'1", maybe?

869
01:01:36,062 --> 01:01:39,062
He has double eyelids, thick eyebrows.

870
01:01:39,062 --> 01:01:42,996
He looks chic when not smiling,
but like a puppy when he does.

871
01:01:42,996 --> 01:01:46,196
You observed him in great detail.

872
01:01:52,362 --> 01:01:54,996
Could it be him you're talking about?

873
01:01:55,962 --> 01:01:57,862
Oh? Manager!

874
01:01:59,229 --> 01:02:01,162
Is she from your company?

875
01:02:06,662 --> 01:02:10,529
Wait, that necklace...

876
01:02:11,696 --> 01:02:15,062
He's a bit older, but a total romantic.

877
01:02:15,062 --> 01:02:16,829
Girlfriend?

878
01:02:19,662 --> 01:02:20,962
You punk.

879
01:02:20,962 --> 01:02:22,662
That's her.

880
01:02:32,696 --> 01:02:33,796
- Se Hyeon.
- What's wrong?

881
01:02:33,796 --> 01:02:36,629
- Is this the punk you were talking about?
- Manager.

882
01:02:37,762 --> 01:02:40,629
Who are you? Do you know what you've done?

883
01:02:40,629 --> 01:02:42,696
Manager, this is my uncle.

884
01:02:42,696 --> 01:02:45,162
That woman who's been haunting
my thoughts since that day.

885
01:02:45,162 --> 01:02:46,196
Ms. Jang Hui Won.

886
01:02:46,196 --> 01:02:49,262
You left the baby's ultrasound photo.

887
01:03:08,296 --> 01:03:11,029
The woman I was searching for

888
01:03:11,696 --> 01:03:13,762
now has a baby.

889
01:03:59,196 --> 01:04:00,396
Am I your baby's father?

890
01:04:00,396 --> 01:04:01,829
Let's just go our separate ways.

891
01:04:01,829 --> 01:04:02,862
Are you going to be a father?

892
01:04:02,862 --> 01:04:04,529
I'm ruined.

893
01:04:04,529 --> 01:04:06,396
Are you really the Jang Hui Won I know?

894
01:04:06,396 --> 01:04:08,662
Do you like him? Are you dating him?

895
01:04:08,662 --> 01:04:11,062
Why is he here?

896
01:04:11,062 --> 01:04:12,129
Wait a minute.

897
01:04:12,129 --> 01:04:14,362
Manager Jang Hui Won,
people will misunderstand.

898
01:04:14,362 --> 01:04:18,162
Ah, you can't do this to me.

899
01:04:18,162 --> 01:04:20,229
No, this is exactly the kind of situation
that invites misunderstanding.

900
01:04:20,229 --> 01:04:21,496
Like falling in love at first sight...

901
01:04:21,496 --> 01:04:22,596
Kang Du Jun?

902
01:04:22,596 --> 01:04:24,429
[Jang Hui Won]
She's pregnant?

903
01:04:24,429 --> 01:04:25,829
How amusing.

904
01:04:25,829 --> 01:04:27,929
Uncle, you're not getting married
because of me, are you?

905
01:04:27,929 --> 01:04:29,929
I'll take responsibility.

906
01:04:29,929 --> 01:04:30,962
Let's get married.

907
01:04:30,962 --> 01:04:32,662
What?
